  "why": "Although the paper reports and quantifies failure cases (e.g., numbers of failed test cases per ASR in Section III.D and examples in Section IV.A) and analyzes the causes of false positives in its own testing framework (Section IV.B), it does not perform any diagnostic analysis of why the ASR models themselves fail. There is no investigation linking failure patterns to underlying model vulnerabilities such as biased training data, reliance on spurious features, or specific phonetic/input structures. The analysis of false positives pertains to Text-To-Speech or preprocessing limitations, not to ASR model weaknesses, and no correlations between failures and input characteristics or model internals are examined. Thus, the paper reports failures but provides no diagnostic insight into their root causes within the ASR models.",
